cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on privacy concerns in online social networks (OSNs) and proposes a graph-based deep learning architecture to infer the current location of a user utilizing only the available information of other social contacts in the OSN. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper deals with privacy concerns in social media platforms and proposes a method to infer the location of a user based on their social contacts. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a graph-based deep learning architecture to learn a model between the users' known and unknown geo-location during a considered period of time. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with privacy concerns in OSNs and proposes a method to infer the location of a user based on their social contacts, which can be considered a security threat. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with the problem of inferring the current location of a user utilizing only the available information of other social contacts in the OSN, which can be considered a form of information retrieval.
